description.narrative:
d.	As a result of profiling and mapping activities, humanitarian and government actors are provided with comprehensive understanding of the characteristics of the IDP communities, including their locations, allowing these actors to better prioritize response capacities.
e.	Protection monitoring conducted on a regular basis by two mobile protection teams in Sa’ada and Hajjah governorates; bi-weekly reports shared and discussed at the protection cluster meetings; 
f.	100 % of IDPs in accessible areas in Sa’ada and Hajjah governorates are registered.  
g.	Some 2,500 families in Al-Mazrak camps 1 and 3 benefit from maintenance and repair of  women centres in Harad;
h.	Non-discrimination is maintained in the provision of assistance for single parent headed HHs, women, children, and elderly people.
